The linear range, sensitivity (slope) and limit of detection (LOD) for the above six samples are shown in Table 1. As can be seen from Table 1, the sensitivity and LOD are significantly improved after loading AO-w, RB-w and AO-RB-w onto ZNAF, indicating that the dispersion state of fluorescent molecules can be improved through immobilization. Accordingly, the detection performance of NO2
                        – ions is remarkably enhanced through immobilization of AO and RB onto ZNAF. AO@ZNAF has the best detection performance, which is significantly better than that reported in the literature (Table 2
                        ).
